# =============================================================================
# [2026-07-14] HED-exit knobs + YPLL/YLL rebuild -- objects expand_pif2 now needs.
# Without these, on another machine the notebook runs but the YPLL section goes
# inert (pif2_ypll_cache = NULL), and the YPLL cannot be rebuilt.
# =============================================================================

# YPLL cache read by the notebook's artifact picker at runtime.
# Dated file = the active 23-cause / 3-metric cache. YPLL.rds = legacy (kept by the
# user's decision, not used; the picker prefers the embedded date so the dated one
# always wins). Tracking the legacy also protects it from an accidental `git clean`.
# Glob covers dated rebuilds (YPLL_YYYYMMDD.rds); YPLL.rds is the legacy (kept).
!Mortalidad/Matrices/YPLL_*.rds
!Mortalidad/Matrices/YPLL.rds

# Rebuild toolchain (so the YPLL can be regenerated from source on any machine).
# The death microdata (DEFUNCIONES_*.parquet), the AAF bundle and the mortality xlsx
# they consume are already whitelisted above.
!__andres_control/build_ypll.R
!__andres_control/ypll_icd_defs.R
!__andres_control/life_tables_20260714.R
!__andres_control/test_ypll_death_base.R
!__andres_control/test_hed_exit_knobs.R
!__andres_control/pif2_hed_exit_chunk_PROPUESTA.md

# Chile HMD period life tables (mortality.org, v6, 2026-01-12), read by
